name: Thai Airways (Unpainted) 777-300ER RTO Sets Off Car Alarms at Paine Field ᴴᴰ
description:
2x GE-90s + parking lot full of cars = ... I'm sure you can guess the outcome :)
You can hear the alarms going off right after the crew slams on the brakes. And by "slams on the brakes", I mean it. If you look at around 1:59-2:00, you can see the entire aircraft jolt forward, putting a lot of force on the nose gear. I did a few slow-motion replays at the end so you can see just how powerful the braking was. Hope you enjoy! :)

Thanks for watching! Please comment, rate, and subscribe!
